# now open your sonarqube ubuntu server
## 4. Install and configure SonarQube:
   - Download and install SonarQube server from the official website.
   - Start the SonarQube server and access the dashboard using `http://localhost:9000`.
   - Configure SonarQube projects and quality gates as per your project requirements.

sudo su
<img width="241" alt="Screenshot 2023-08-03 215737" src="https://github.com/MagdaleneMensah/DevopsmyAWS/assets/133181270/2947ccf2-7c43-4563-9325-ec469113d6d0">

hostname Sonarqube
<img width="362" alt="Screenshot 2023-08-03 225402" src="https://github.com/MagdaleneMensah/DevopsmyAWS/assets/133181270/0640cb7a-efde-4dea-a1f2-4b843ece1e2d">

bash
<img width="267" alt="Screenshot 2023-08-03 225526" src="https://github.com/MagdaleneMensah/DevopsmyAWS/assets/133181270/983325b2-21ee-4219-aa01-9f4af00db273">

## 5. Integrate Jenkins with SonarQube:
    - Install SonarQube Scanner plugin in Jenkins and configure it with the SonarQube server URL and access token.
    - Add a SonarQube analysis stage in your pipeline or a build step in your Freestyle project.

